result.execSummary:
The defendant Nartavious Parker was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Vehicle Operator Flee/Elude Officer, a class I felony, Wisconsin Statutes 346.04(3).
  • Theft-Movable Property >$2500-$5000, a class I felony, Wisconsin Statutes 943.20(1)(a).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Defendant Nartavious Parker in court with attorney Cheryl Anne Ward.  Defendant Nartavious Parker in custody.  Jeremy R. Arn appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Defendant was advised of constitutional rights and maximum penalties, waived all rights, plead GUILTY to both counts and was examined as to the plea.  Plea Questionnaire/Waiver of Rights and Addendum received and filed.  Parties stipulate to the complaint as a factual basis for the plea.  Defendant further advised that if he is not a US citizen deportation is possible.  Court found defendant guilty on both counts as charged in the Information and ordered entry of Judgment of Conviction.

AS TO COUNT 1:
The Court sentenced defendant to serve a term of IMPRISONMENT in the Wisconsin State Prisons for 33 MONTHS.  INITIAL CONFINEMENT of 15 MONTHS and EXTENDED SUPERVISION of 18 MONTHS, consecutive to COUNT 2, with credit for 2 days time served.  Court STAYED sentence and placed the defendant on PROBATION for a period of 3 1/2 YEARS with the following conditions:
Defendant is eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program and is not eligible for the Wisconsin Substance Abuse Program.
-Restitution set at $0 
-Defendant to pay Court costs and all applicable surcharges and assessments to be collected during term probation; nonpayment penalty shall be a civil judgment
-Defendant to pay attorney fees and costs at the rate of $50.00 per month starting 6-1-2016; nonpayment penalty shall be a civil judgment
-Defendant is to provide a DNA sample and pay the related surcharge to be collected during term of probation; nonpayment penalty shall result in a civil judgment
-No new law violations rising to the level of probable cause
-No association with drug users, drug dealers and drug houses or otherwise engage in drug dealing
-Cooperate with agent
-Obtain/maintain employment unless in school.  If in school full-time, defendant to have a part-time job 
-Obtain GED or HSED
-Successfully complete a Cognitive Thinking Behavioral Modification Program
-Anger management assessment; cooperate with any treatment deemed appropriate
-No contact with Rosen Nissan located at 5505 S. 27th Street, Milwaukee 
-AODA assessment and any recommended treatment
-Absolute sobriety with random urine screens and breathalyzers
-No alcohol or controlled substances
-As a condition of probation, Court ordered defendant serve 9 MONTHS in the House of Corrections, with Huber release privileges for work/treatment programs.  No good time credit.  No electronic monitoring.  Defendant to report to the House of Corrections on 8-27-2015 at 1:00 p.m.

AS TO COUNT 2:
The Court sentenced defendant to serve a term of IMPRISONMENT in the Wisconsin State Prisons for 30 MONTHS.  INITIAL CONFINEMENT of 12 MONTHS and EXTENDED SUPERVISION of 18 MONTHS, consecutive to COUNT 1.  Court STAYED sentence and placed the defendant on PROBATION for a period of 3 1/2 YEARS with the following conditions:
Defendant is eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program and is not eligible for the Wisconsin Substance Abuse Program.
